Sentencas: While ceramic anodes provide a path to overcome the obstacles of the current state of the art cermet-based solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), they are limited by processing challenges, low conductivity, poor catalytic activity, and instability.
Titulo: Catalyst-Exsolving Anode-Supported Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Here, we address these challenges by fabricating a ceramic-anode-supported SOFC composed of Sr2Fe0.4Ni0.8Mo0.8O6-delta (SFNM) which is highly conductive and spontaneously exsolves nano-catalysts for low temperature operation (600 degrees C).
Titulo: Catalyst-Exsolving Anode-Supported Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Using a simple and scalable procedure, we manufacture these SOFCs to have 60% lower ohmic loss than their electrolyte-supported analogues and we take advantage of the in-situ catalyst exsolution to circumvent additional catalyst deposition steps.
Titulo: Catalyst-Exsolving Anode-Supported Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: We show that the catalyst exsolution triples the peak power density up to similar to 200 mW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C with H-2 fuel, which is comparable to other ceramic anode SOFCs operating at considerably higher temperatures (>700 degrees C).
Titulo: Catalyst-Exsolving Anode-Supported Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Further, we discuss two major challenges facing exsolution-anode supported SOFCs, show our efforts to identify and address the root causes of such problems, and describe a potential path forward for next-generation anodes.
Titulo: Catalyst-Exsolving Anode-Supported Low-Temperature Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
